org.tsugi.impl.jdbc

Class Tsugi_JDBC

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tsugi.base.BaseTsugi
      • org.tsugi.impl.jdbc.Tsugi_JDBC
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Tsugi

    public class Tsugi_JDBC
extends BaseTsugi
implements Tsugi
    The implementation for Tsugi and JDBC launch factory This is where the major work of the JDBC reference implementation happens. This is configured by several properties: 
    
 tsugi.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:8889/tsugi
 tsugi.datasource.username=ltiuser
 tsugi.datasource.password=ltipassword
 tsugi.datasource.driverClassName=com.mysql.jdbc.Driver
    These properties are first checked from the system-wide properties and then a properties file of /tsugi.properties is read from the class path. All properties must come from the same source. There is a lot of work that happens in this class.

        public Connection getConnection()
        Description copied from interface: Tsugi
        Return a database connection for use by Tsugi. This should only be used for maintenance and non-launch related database access. The normal path is to get the launch and then pull the connection from the Launch structure. this way we don't make more connections than we need.

      • adjustData

        public void adjustData(Connection c,
                       Properties row,
                       Properties post)
        Make sure that the data in our lti_ tables matches the POST data This routine compares the POST data with the data pulled from the lti_ tables and goes through carefully INSERTing or UPDATING all the nexessary data in the lti_ tables to make sure that the lti_ table correctly match all the data from the incoming post. While this looks like a lot of INSERT and UPDATE statements, the INSERT statements only run when we see a new user/course/link for the first time and after that, we only update is something changes. So in a high percentage of launches we are not seeing any new or updated data and so this code just falls through and does absolutely no SQL.
